Conclusion:
Because the jangly pop‑rock CD aligns with nearly every specific production and arrangement preference I listed (hooks, chiming guitars that lift, forward vocals and harmonies, transparent midrange, clean mastering that preserves dynamics and avoids over‑compression), and because The Captain and the Kid emphasizes the close‑miked, hushy, quietly shaded aesthetics I explicitly said reduce immediacy and melodic focus, I choose the jangly pop‑rock singles CD and reject The Captain and the Kid.

