The user updates his self-description as follows: I prefer immediate, melody‑first heartland/jangly rock—compact, hooky arrangements with driving mid‑tempo propulsion, chiming but assertive electric guitars, warm rhythmic snap, and singalong choruses. I want intimate yet energetic vocals that sit forward without breathy close‑miking; clear lead presence and harmonies in a transparent midrange. Production should feel live‑in‑the‑room but polished, preserving dynamics and punch without over‑compression; tasteful reverb rather than cavernous arena wash. I value natural instrument timbre—punchy drums, woody acoustic/piano warmth, and guitar tone with character rather than excessive distortion. I dislike hushy, ultra‑close‑miked folk intimacy, static quiet dynamic shading, diffuse mixes that sap immediacy, and spectacle‑first, over‑compressed or arena‑grandiose productions that bury vocal nuance.

